modules.description: This module supports operations for managing ordered string-keyed maps, focusing on key-value pair manipulation (insertion, deletion, lookup), structural transformations (merging, filtering, partitioning), and ordered traversal (iteration, folding in key order). It works with maps where keys are strings and values can be arbitrary types, including specialized handling for lists as values via `add_to_list`. Common use cases include processing multipart form data with string keys, aggregating values into lists, and maintaining ordered key-value associations for serialization or incremental processing.

This module parses and processes multipart/form-data streams, extracting named parts and files while handling boundary alignment and part metadata retrieval. It provides operations to stream file or string data from individual parts, supporting use cases like handling HTTP form submissions with file uploads. The module includes a submodule for managing ordered string-keyed maps, enabling key-value manipulation, structural transformations, and ordered traversal, with specialized handling for list-valued entries via `add_to_list`. Together, these components support efficient, structured processing of multipart data with string keys and mixed-value types, including aggregation into lists and incremental traversal.
